# arvo-sparse — backlog

> **Type-surface reminder**: new entries use `arvo::USize` /
> `Bool` / `UFixed<N, 0, S>` instead of `usize` / `bool` / `u*`;
> `notko::Maybe` / `Outcome` instead of `Option` / `Result`. See
> `rules/type-surface.md`.

## BitMatrix256 / Mask256 variants

`rcm_reorder`, `block_diagonal`, `dulmage_mendelsohn` all have
`Mask256`-backed siblings that share the algorithmic shape with the
`Mask64` impls shipped this round. Promote when a concrete consumer
surfaces >64-node adjacency. Same abstraction-vs-duplication trade-off
note as arvo-graph: on current nightly, keep two copies rather than
force a trait abstraction that fights `generic_const_exprs`.

## SpMV

Sparse matrix-vector multiply patterns. Deferred per the original
design (polka-dots T3 decisions #71-74). Same representation and API
surface as the above algorithms; add when a concrete consumer need
surfaces.

## cap_size helper promotion to arvo L0

arvo-sparse imports `cap_size` from arvo-bitmask. When a third L2 /
L3 crate needs the same `Cap -> usize` unwrap (arvo-graph already
does after the 202604260000 cascade; arvo-spectral has a local copy;
arvo-comb would be the tipping point), promote the helper into arvo
L0 as a public `const fn`. Purely additive; removes the cross-crate
import chain on a trivially small helper.
